<!DOCTYPE task PUBLIC "-//OASIS//DTD DITA Task//EN" "task.dtd">
<task id="reboot_instance">
    <title>Migrate an Instance</title>
    <shortdesc/>
    <prolog>
        <metadata>
            <keywords>
                <indexterm>Maintenance</indexterm>
                <indexterm>Instances <indexterm>migrating</indexterm>
                </indexterm>
            </keywords>
        </metadata>
    </prolog>
    <taskbody>
        <context>
            <p>Eucalyptus allows you to migrate an instance between Node
                Controllers (NCs). This is sometimes necessary to perform system
                maintenance, or to balance system requirements with available
                resources.</p>
        </context>
        <steps>
            <step>
                <cmd>To migrate an instance to another NC, enter the following command:</cmd>
                <info>
                    <codeblock>euca-migrate-instances -i [instance_id]</codeblock>
                </info>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>To migrate an instance to a specific NC, enter the following command:</cmd>
                <info>
                    <codeblock>euca-migrate-instances -i [instance_id] --dest=[NC IP address]</codeblock>
                </info>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>To migrate an instance <i>avoiding</i> a specific NC, enter
                    the following command:</cmd>
                <info>
                    <codeblock>euca-migrate-instances -i [instance_id] --exclude-dest=[NC IP address]</codeblock>
                </info>
            </step>
        </steps>
        <example>
            <p>To migrate the instance <codeph>i-34523332</codeph> to the NC on 10.1.1.45, enter:</p>
            <codeblock>euca-migrate-instances i-34523332 --dest=10.1.1.45</codeblock>
        </example>
    </taskbody>
</task>
